  "instructions": [
    "Preheat your oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "Slice the Brioche Bread into 1-inch thick slices and place on a baking sheet.",
    "Drizzle the Extra Virgin Olive Oil over the bread slices and toast in the oven for 5-7 minutes, or until lightly browned.",
    "Meanwhile, mash the Avocado in a bowl with a fork and mix in the Sweet Chilli Sauce, Orange Juice, Cinnamon, and a pinch of Salt and Pepper.",
    "Remove the toasted bread from the oven and let cool for a minute or two.",
    "Spread a layer of the Avocado mixture onto each toasted bread slice.",
    "Place the bread slices under the broiler for an additional 30-60 seconds, or until the top is lightly browned.",
    "Remove the bread from the oven and garnish with Fresh Cilantro Leaves.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy!"
  ],
